        <div id="text" class="left-part description wow slideInLeft">
          <div class="header">
            Contents controls the IDE
          </div>
          <div class="text">
            The Guides editor fully controls the IDE. Each page is able to open and close the files
            you need to see for any individual page of content. You can also execute commands, open
            up browser pages and even highlight portions of code.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="middle-part">
          <div id="row1" class="vertical-dot-line">
            <div class="top"></div>
            <div class="dot"></div>
            <div class="bottom"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="img" class="right-part screen wow slideInRight">
          <%= image_tag 'assets/features/curriculum/content-1.png', alt: 'Guides controls IDE', class: 'img-responsive' %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="row">
      <div class="line-mobile">
        <div class="dot"></div>
